      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Herb Yellin (1935-2014) was an American book collector and publisher.  He founded Lord John Press in 1976 to publish signed limited editions of significant American authors.  Joyce Carol Oates (1938- ) is a an award-winning American author of fiction and non-fiction, including novels, short stories, poems, plays, and essays.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Herb Yellin Papers Relating to Joyce Carol Oates</emph> consists of correspondence, memorabilia and printed material relating to Yellin's Lord John Press and to author Joyce Carol Oates, several of whose short works were published by Yellin.  The collection two folders of detailed and friendly personal correspondence between Yellin and Oates.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
